#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.85"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.85:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.85:0.2"
msgid "9. Sītivagga"
msgstr "9. Coolness"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.85:0.3"
msgid "85. Sītibhāvasutta"
msgstr "85. Coolness"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.85:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Chahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu abhabbo anuttaraṃ sītibhāvaṃ "
"sacchikātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant with six qualities can’t realize supreme coolness."

msgctxt "an6.85:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi chahi?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.85:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ niggahetabbaṃ tasmiṃ samaye "
"cittaṃ na niggaṇhāti, yasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ paggahetabbaṃ tasmiṃ samaye "
"cittaṃ na paggaṇhāti, yasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ sampahaṃsitabbaṃ tasmiṃ samaye "
"cittaṃ na sampahaṃseti, yasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ ajjhupekkhitabbaṃ tasmiṃ samaye "
"cittaṃ na ajjhupekkhati, hīnādhimuttiko ca hoti, sakkāyābhirato ca."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t keep their mind in check when they should. "
"They don’t exert their mind when they should. They don’t encourage the mind "
"when they should. They don’t watch over the mind with equanimity when they "
"should. They believe in low things. They love identity."

msgctxt "an6.85:1.4"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, chahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu abhabbo anuttaraṃ "
"sītibhāvaṃ sacchikātuṃ."
msgstr "A mendicant with these six qualities can’t realize supreme coolness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.85:2.1"
msgid ""
"Chahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhabbo anuttaraṃ sītibhāvaṃ "
"sacchikātuṃ."
msgstr "A mendicant with six qualities can realize supreme coolness."

msgctxt "an6.85:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi chahi?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.85:2.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu yasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ niggahetabbaṃ tasmiṃ samaye "
"cittaṃ niggaṇhāti, yasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ paggahetabbaṃ tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ "
"paggaṇhāti, yasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ sampahaṃsitabbaṃ tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ "
"sampahaṃseti, yasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ ajjhupekkhitabbaṃ tasmiṃ samaye cittaṃ "
"ajjhupekkhati, paṇītādhimuttiko ca hoti nibbānābhirato ca."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant keeps their mind in check when they should. They exert "
"their mind when they should. They encourage the mind when they should. They "
"watch over the mind with equanimity when they should. They are committed to "
"the sublime. They delight in extinguishment."

msgctxt "an6.85:2.4"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, chahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu bhabbo anuttaraṃ "
"sītibhāvaṃ sacchikātun”ti."
msgstr "A mendicant with these six qualities can realize supreme coolness.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.85:2.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
